cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new architecture for neural networks that reduces the number of trainable parameters while maintaining performance. It may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it deals with neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sparse coding techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the proposed architecture is inspired by spatially-coupled sparse constructions, which may fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
